title: Google\Cloud\Talent\V4\DebugOptions
name: DebugOptions
description:
Various debug options available for debugging mode. Internal only.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.talent.v4.DebugOptions

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.level
params.description: Specifies the level of debug output. The higher the number, the more debug information is returned and printed in backend server logs. Current levels are 1-4.

params.name: data.searcher
params.description: Specifies which search backend to use. Current available options are: st-bti, model-t, and st-muppet.

params.name: data.scoring_parameter_override
params.description: Specifies the scoring parameters to override during search. This is equivalent to the 'dsp' url parameter in the legacy system. For details, consult go/gjobs-scoring-params.

params.name: data.search_all_tenant
params.description: Search documents of all tenants (only implemented for job search as of 6/14/2019).

params.name: data.enable_wildcard_search
params.description: Temporarily added this flag for profile wildcard search Flag to indicate whether wildcard search is enabled
